Write a docstring for how to use this CTA tracker in our HTML templates.
Here's a docstring that explains how to use this CTA tracker in HTML templates:

```javascript
/**
 * CTA (Call-to-Action) Tracker
 * 
 * This module provides automatic tracking of user interactions with various clickable elements
 * on the page, such as buttons, links, and accordions. It sends tracking events to Google Analytics
 * or logs them to the console if GA is not available.
 * 
 * Usage in HTML templates:
 * 
 * 1. Basic tracking:
 *    The tracker automatically tracks clicks on <a>, <button>, and elements with class .btn
 *    Example: <a href="/example">Click me</a>
 * 
 * 2. Custom CTA name:
 *    Use the 'data-cta-tracker-name' attribute to specify a custom name for the CTA
 *    Example: <button data-cta-tracker-name="Submit Form">Submit</button>
 * 
 * 3. Fallback naming:
 *    If no custom name is provided, the tracker uses the following attributes in order:
 *    title, aria-label, and then falls back to the element's inner text
 *    Example: <a href="/example" title="Learn More">Click here</a>
 * 
 * 4. Accordion tracking:
 *    Elements with the 'data-toggle' attribute are tracked as accordions
 *    Example: <div data-toggle="collapse">Expand section</div>
 * 
 * 5. Preventing double tracking:
 *    The tracker adds 'data-cta-tracker-configured' to elements it has set up.
 *    To prevent an element from being tracked, add this attribute manually:
 *    Example: <button data-cta-tracker-configured>Don't track me</button>
 * 
 * Note: The tracker automatically sets up on page load and continues to check for
 * new elements every second for 10 seconds to catch dynamically added content.
 */
```

This docstring provides a comprehensive guide on how to use the CTA tracker in HTML templates, covering basic usage, custom naming, fallback behavior, special cases like accordions, and how to prevent tracking if needed. It also notes the automatic setup behavior, which is useful for developers to understand how the tracker works with dynamically added content.
